Dialogue: 10,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.31,Caption,,0,0,0,,This is how a decade of work and three\Nhundred
Dialogue: 10,0:00:03.31,0:00:06.62,Caption,,0,0,0,,and seventy million dollars came apart\Nin less time than
Dialogue: 10,0:00:06.62,0:00:08.60,Caption,,0,0,0,,it takes to read this sentence.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:08.94,0:00:10.67,Caption,,0,0,0,,This is POST-MORTEM.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:11.01,0:00:14.00,Caption,,0,0,0,,Ariane 5 was Europe's bet on the future.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:14.34,0:00:18.25,Caption,,0,0,0,,Its predecessor, Ariane 4, was one of\Nthe most reliable
Dialogue: 10,0:00:18.25,0:00:21.76,Caption,,0,0,0,,rockets ever flown — Europe's workhorse,\Na machine that
Dialogue: 10,0:00:21.76,0:00:25.28,Caption,,0,0,0,,put more than half the world's\Ncommercial satellites into
Dialogue: 10,0:00:25.28,0:00:29.18,Caption,,0,0,0,,orbit. But it was getting old, and it\Nwasn't big
Dialogue: 10,0:00:29.18,0:00:31.52,Caption,,0,0,0,,enough for what was coming next.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:31.86,0:00:35.94,Caption,,0,0,0,,So the European Space Agency spent\Nnearly ten years and
Dialogue: 10,0:00:35.94,0:00:38.80,Caption,,0,0,0,,around seven billion dollars building\Nits successor.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:38.80,0:00:42.88,Caption,,0,0,0,,Ariane 5 was taller, heavier, and far\Nmore powerful —
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.88,0:00:46.97,Caption,,0,0,0,,a rocket designed to carry the biggest\Npayloads of the
Dialogue: 10,0:00:46.97,0:00:47.78,Caption,,0,0,0,,coming century.
